Example 1: Creating a ZFS File System Hierarchy
       The following commands create a file system named pool/home and a file system named pool/home/bob.  The mount point /export/home is set for the parent file sys‚Äê
       tem, and is automatically inherited by the child file system.
             # zfs create pool/home
             # zfs set mountpoint=/export/home pool/home

